The FIFA World Cup is due to be held in Qatar from 21 November to 18 December 2022.
Qatari authorities are still finalising entry requirements and how access to the tournament and affiliated venues will be managed. If you’re planning to attend the World Cup, you may wish to delay making travel arrangements until requirements are confirmed.
If you’re planning to travel to Qatar for the World Cup you should sign up for email alerts to the Qatar Travel Advice page to stay up to date on the latest information. In line with previous tournaments the FCDO will communicate with fans ahead of the World Cup to provide them with simple advice and tips.
